1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new method for cooperation and underlay mode selection in cognitive radio networks, which involves the use of networking and internet architecture concepts. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper characterizes the maximum achievable throughput of the proposed method, which involves the use of information theory concepts. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the use of cognitive radio networks, which involves the use of cryptography and security concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model for regulating hybrid access through monitoring the state of the primary link, which involves the use of systems and control concepts. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an action-reward model for opportunistic spectrum access, which involves the use of artificial intelligence concepts.
